NAK Only about 50 of the rhenium is recovered by shipping the moly concentrate to China for conventional smelting but if Trump were to subsidize the construction of a hydrometallurgical smelter at Pebble about 90 would be recoverable as well as most of the tellurium which the Pebble claims are expected to have an enormous amount of according to the US Geological Service Not only would it be great for the US but also great for the bottom line The hydrometallurgical smelter would have to have sufficient capacity to handle all of Pebbles smelting needs The beauty of hydrometallurgical smelting is that it is also much more environmentally friendly than conventional smelting Perhaps someone who knows something about smelting could weigh in on this topic
